    • Frequently Asked Questions

    Q. When and where can I take a test drive?
    You can schedule test drives at any time that suits you, either at a Spinny hub or via a book Home test drive option on website. After you submit the booking request, a relationship manager will call to confirm the schedule and location.
    Q. Whats the process for booking my car?
    You can book an Assured & Budget car of your liking for up to 5 days by placing a refundable deposit of Rs. 20,000. Similarly, for Spinny Max cars, it's Rs. 50,000. If you complete the vehicle purchase within the holding period, the deposit will be applied toward the purchase; otherwise, it will be refunded to you, and the booking will be cancelled.
    Q. Will Spinny help me with car finance?
    Absolutely, buyers can choose to avail financing through Spinny wherein we would get the loan processed through our finance partners. Our established partnerships help us process loans faster and get our customers better interest rates. Depending on your credit worthiness, you can avail used car loans through Spinny at interest rates as low as 12.99% compared to the market rates of 14-16%.
    Q. How does Spinny's money back guarantee work?
    At Spinny we are only happy when youre happy. So if you don't absolutely love your new Spinny car you can return it back within 5 days and upto 300km of running (from the date of delivery) and your complete purchase amount will be refunded back to you within 7-9 working days, no-questions-asked.
    Q.Are all cars on Spinny inspected before listing?
    Yes, every car listed on Spinny goes through a detailed used car inspection before being made available. The inspection covers key areas like engine condition, body, interiors, documents, and car condition so buyers can make an informed decision.

    Ground clearance

    The vertical distance between the flat surface on which the car is standing (with tyres correctly inflated) and the lowest point on the car's chassis.

    Wheelbase

    The horizontal distance between the centres of the front and the rear tyres.

    Kerb weight

    Weight of the vehicle including a full tank of fuel & all standard equipment. Doesn't include the weight of passengers, cargo or optional equipment.

    Drivetrain

    The chain of components that deliver power from the engine to the tyres.

    Displacement

    Defines the size of an engine. It is the volume of the cylinder when the piston is at the lowermost point multiplied by the no. of cylinders.

    Number of cylinders

    The number of cylinders present in an engine. This number depends on the purpose served by the engine.

    Limited slip differential (LSD)

    Maintains minimum torque on both wheels of an axle, & redistributes the rest based on road restrictions, thus offering better control on rough or slippery roads.

    Turbocharger

    Pushes more air inside the cylinder for better combustion of fuel. It's powered by the exhaust gases that come out of an engine.

    Multi drive modes

    Changes car behaviour based on driver selection to provide economical, sporty or comfortable drives.

    Mileage (ARAI)

    Mileage of a car determined by ARAI on a designated test track; may vary from mileage figures achieved in actual driving conditions.

    Max power (bhp)

    Maximum power refers to the maximum measured horsepower output of an engine at rated speeds as stated by the manufacturer.

    Max torque (Nm)

    Maximum torque is the highest value of the net torque measured at full engine load.

    Steering adjustment type

    Tilt: 'Up' and 'down' change in position of the steering wheel; Telescopic: 'In' and 'out' movement of the steering wheel.

    Electronic parking brake

    A feature that allows you to engage or disengage the handbrake with the press of a button instead of pulling the lever.

    Airbags

    Minimises impact during an accident by inflating a baloon-like bag that acts as a cushion to soften the blow to passengers and reducing risk of serious injury.

    Rear camera

    Makes reversing the car easier, as it gives you a clear view of what's behind you.

    Cruise control

    Allows you to drive at constant speed without pressing the accelerator; useful for highway driving. On pressing brakes, feature is deactivated for safety.

    Keyless start

    Allows you to turn on the car's engine without inserting the keys into the ignition. You only need to press the start/ stop button & keep the key in the car with you.

    Sunroof
